node.title: NSW breaks COVID-19 case record with 1,742 new infections
node.alt: A COVID-19 information sign with the Sydney Opera House pictured in the background.
node.description: NSW recorded 1,742 new COVID-19 cases in the 24 hours to 8:00pm yesterday.
node.content: ["NSW recorded 1,742 new COVID-19 cases in the 24 hours to 8:00pm yesterday.", "It's\u00a0the highest number ever recorded in the state in a day, breaking NSW's previous peak of 1,603 on September 11.", "A total of 192 people are in hospital with the virus, including 26 in ICU.", "There were no deaths in the reporting period.", "NSW's daily figure is also higher than Victoria's for the first time in months.", "Victoria today announced 1,622 new COVID-19 infections in its latest 24-hour reporting period.", "Yesterday, the state lifted restrictions for the unvaccinated after effectively keeping them in lockdown for months.", "People who were yet to receive both doses of the COVID-19 vaccine are now able to receive household visitors, sit down in hospitality venues and go shopping in non-essential retail businesses.", "NSW Health Minister Brad Hazzard warned yesterday the state could see up to 25,000 COVID-19 cases per day next month, citing modelling from the University of New South Wales (UNSW).", "He said the modelling was still being fine tuned and the algorithms were based on what was happening in the UK and southern Africa.", "\"So we may not get to 25,000 cases a day, but we could,\" he said.", "More to come."]
